<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-11-27T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-11-27T12:00:00-05:00" n="1105" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1105">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/9932.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to
                                    Germany</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-27T18:00:00+01:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1913—6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The comments of the Foreign Office on Mexico are that there must be some
                            one to succeed Huerta and that meanwhile German interests are suffering
                            terribly. If they can find a good excuse, I think there is a chance of
                            persuading the Government to withdraw all recognition of Huerta.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>